CCH - The Cellulose and Paper Manufactory was built in 1972 (under the name of CELROM, at the time) in order to use abundant wood resources (beech and poplar essences) from the southwest of the country and along the Danube river.

Today, we are the only company in Romania specialized in the production of semi-chemical core paper with wood fiber content, with an annual production capacity of 80,000 tons of paper, with weights ranging from 112-200 g / m².

We are proud of the large portfolio of both national and international clients from all fields of activity, because we can create intelligent and very good quality solutions in any of our specialties:

- manufacture of semi-cellulose from deciduous wood (the only factory in the country and one of the few in Europe);

- manufacture of semi-chemical fluting paper assortments, intended for making corrugated cardboard packaging for vegetables and fruits, pizza, electronics and automotive (gearboxes, gearboxes, etc.);

- manufacture of corrugated cardboard and corrugated cardboard packaging.

Créé il y a plus de 60 ans, VEYRIERE Groupe est un des principaux scieurs auvergnats de résineux. Implantée à Arlanc (63), l’entité familiale compte aujourd’hui 70 salariés. Le groupe rassemble plusieurs activités de sciage et de transformation qui lui permettent de réaliser un chiffre d’affaires de 20 millions d’euros. 
Grâce à la complémentarité de ses activités, le groupe transforme et valorise l’ensemble de ses matières premières et s’inscrit aujourd’hui dans une démarche pauvre en déchets. Fort d’une gestion forestière locale et responsable, la société se positionne comme un acteur investi dans l’innovation. 


Le groupe est constitué de différentes sociétés : 

-       SCIERIE VEYRIERE, spécialisée dans les sciages
-	UTB, spécialisée dans les bois collés, lame de terrasses et autres produits finis traités en autoclaves ; 
-	VEYRIERE CHARPENTE, spécialisée dans la construction et l’installation de charpentes en bois ; 
-	SOVEYPAL, produit des débit-palettes ; 
-	VBE, usine de cogénération biomasse et qui fabrique des granulés.

Somos uma empresa que prioriza dois fatores: inovação e confiança. Fatores, aliás, que estão intrínsecos ao sucesso do nosso negócio.

Inovamos para estar sempre na vanguarda e oferecer a nossos clientes o que há de melhor e mais novo no mercado, entregando produtos que aliem um ótimo acabamento com o respeito ao meio ambiente .Hoje, temos o prazer de ver nossos produtos se tornarem uma referência de qualidade no segmento.

Mas somente inovar não basta para tornar uma empresa perene. Por isso, sempre investimos na capacitação de nossa equipe para que possamos mostrar o quanto somos uma empresa que preza pela confiança, que cumpre prazos, cuida da entrega dos produtos com toda segurança, entre outras boas práticas.

Foi essa união entre inovação e confiança que fez a Agaprint uma empresa consolidada, com mais de trinta anos no mercado e a maior empresa brasileira no ramo de fabricação e comercialização de envelopes e formulários contínuos, agora com a novidade da fabricação de bobinas de PDV e papel carbono.

Nossos princípios:

- Relações de qualidade;

- Responsabilidade;

- Iniciativa e conhecimento;

- Comprometimento;

- Confiança e inovação

Depuis 1952, notre connaissance approfondie du bois, de son origine géographique, de sa transformation et de ses utilisations, nous permet de vous proposer des sciages résineux de qualité correspondant à chacune de vos demandes.

Nous rejoindre, c’est intégrer une entreprise familiale, associée à des équipements industriels modernes permettant d'assurer à nos clients des bois de qualité !

Nos 3 sites de production regroupent : 
•	A Dunières, Une scierie moderne; 
•	A Montregard, Un parc à grumes à la pointe de la technologie, Une Raboterie, ainsi que 2 séchoirs à gaz ;
•	A Roche la Molière, Une usine de granules de bois.

- Líder nacional na produção de embalagens alimentares para ovos em papel reciclado;
- Comercialização  de outros tipos de embalagens alimentares;
- PME excelencia;
- Empresa certificada pela qualidade e pelo ambiente.

La société Intersac Développement est basée à Saint Junien, au cœur du Limousin en Nouvelle Aquitaine, région historique d’implantation de l’industrie papier carton. Implantée depuis plus de 50 ans sur le même site, l’usine est spécialisée dans la fabrication de sacs et sachets en papier neutre ou entièrement personnalisables.

Intersac fournit tous les secteurs d’activité : artisanat et industrie, agriculture, commerce de bouche et de détail, événementiel… Nous donnons la priorité aux petites et moyennes séries afin de faciliter les circuits courts et le turn-over idéal chez les clients.

Nos engagements & valeurs :

- Recruter et former ses collaborateurs localement pour favoriser l’emploi régional ;

- Fournir à nos clients un conseil technique adapté en matière de conception et de format ;

- Valoriser la fabrication française et les circuits courts ;

- Contribuer aux efforts de développement durable en veillant à recycler l’intégralité des matières premières utilisées en production.

Species of trees: pine, spruce, fir, oak, beech, ash etc.
Products:
floor boards;
biulding boards;
parquet workpiesces;
pallete workpiesces;
furniture boards;
glued window beams; 
etc.

Jackaroo is an industrial merchant located in Sydney and Johannesburg supplying customers in Australia, New Zealand, South East Asia, China, and Southern Africa. The company was founded in 1988 and began trading with the support of a number of specialty paper manufacturers in Europe. Today, Jackaroo imports paper from US, Europe and South America and is a leading importer of paper into the country.

Jackaroo provides flexible services to its customers by a way of:

*  knowledgeable sales & customer service staff;
*  sales forecasting software;
*  state of the art import order management system;
*  co-ordination of customs clearance, AQIS inspections;
*  warehousing, storage and delivery stock management and consignment supply.

Codima is a Portuguese company, based in Ermesinde and focuses on the development of various codification, marking and industrial identification solutions. We operate in this market since 1997 and focus mainly on industrial production, for which we possess all the necessary equipment following the highest quality standards.

Our solutions:
- Hardware;
- Software development;
- Identification, codification and labeling services;
- Pre and after-sale, monitoring and training.

The paper production was started in the factory in October 2007. The production of paper based on recycled fibers is carried out on the flat net machine with the trim width of 2550 mm, max drive speed 800 m \ min, max capacity up to 200 tones per 24 h.

The paper production department equipped with modern facilities that ensure the compliance with the modern parameters of technological regulations as well as a high degree of automatic control: 

-	fractionation and refining system; 
-	improved system of pulp preparation, the modern four-stage vortex pulp cleaning system was installed; 
-	scanner for the paper and cardboard quality control; 
-	sizer \ glue press which allows the surface treatment by the application of the adhesive on the basis of modified starch, that along with the exception of intro-pulp sizing significantly improves the barrier properties and strength of the product; 

After several stages of modernization, the existing equipment completely covers the own needs of the enterprise in the fluting and greyboards for flat layers allows you to close up the production cycle – from the waste paper to the ready made cardboard box – and to sell the major part of the products either in the domestic market or to export. 
Our own certification laboratory enables us to measure all the physical and mechanical properties of paper and cardboard (CMT, CCT, SCT, FCT, RCT, Cobb etc.) that are of significant importance both for the Ukrainian and foreign customers. 
A reasonable price-performance ratio of our cardboard and paper allows the company to be among the leaders on the domestic market and to successfully cooperate with the European and the CIS countries.

«Kuvert-Ukraine»– is a Ukrainian element of the biggest European envelope manufacturer concern «Mayer Kuvert Network» . This fact gives our company a number of significant advantages:
— production capacity of more than 30 factories in Europe – 70 million envelopes every day;
— centralized stable supply of raw materials of the highest quality;
— experience, accumulated for decades, which we are always willing to share with our partners.
For cooperation with us we reward you with sustainable partnership, coordinated staff work and innovations in the area of the promotional envelope.  During one shift we produce about 800 thousand envelopes.

Much attention being paid to our product quality. Our company is certified by international quality system ISO 9001:2009.

Envelope - it's not just a package for your letter, but:
- successful presentation of your company;
- integrated part of promotional mailing on which it most depends whether your letter is going to be read or not;
- just-in-time delivery of your correspondence.
We are the team that doesn't stop on the achieved.
We are continiously working at improving and expanding our business offers. Cooperate with professionals, because for us Impossible is Possible.
